  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I embed a Prezi into an HTML email?",
  "response": "Embedding a Prezi into an HTML email is not straightforward because most email clients do not support embedded iframes or JavaScript, which are commonly used to embed Prezi presentations. However, you can still share your Prezi effectively in an email by using a link and a thumbnail image. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### Step-by-Step Guide:\n\n1. **Create a Shareable Link for Your Prezi:**\n   - Go to your Prezi presentation.\n   - Click on the **Share** button.\n   - Copy the shareable link (you can choose to make it public or restrict access as needed).\n\n2. **Create a Thumbnail Image for Your Prezi:**\n   - Take a screenshot of your Prezi (e.g., the first slide or a key visual).\n   - Save the image file (e.g., `prezi-thumbnail.jpg`).\n\n3. **Insert the Link and Thumbnail in Your HTML Email:**\n   Use HTML to insert the thumbnail image and link it to your Prezi. Here\u2019s an example:\n\n   ```html\n   <a href=\"https://your-prezi-link-here\" target=\"_blank\">\n       <img src=\"https://your-image-host-url/prezi-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"View My Prezi Presentation\" style=\"border: none; display: block; max-width: 100%;\">\n   </a>\n   <p style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; color: #555;\">\n       <a href=\"https://your-prezi-link-here\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #0073e6; text-decoration: none;\">View My Prezi Presentation</a>\n   </p>\n   ```\n\n   Replace `https://your-prezi-link-here` with your actual Prezi link and `https://your-image-host-url/prezi-thumbnail.jpg` with the URL where your thumbnail image is hosted.\n\n4. **Test Your Email:**\n   - Send a test email to yourself and check how it renders in different email clients (e.g., Gmail, Outlook, Apple Mail).\n   - Ensure the image is clickable and redirects to your Prezi.\n\n### Tips:\n\u0915\u0940\u091f- **Image Hosting:** Use a reliable image hosting service or upload the thumbnail to your website to ensure the image is accessible.\n\u0915\u0940\u091f- **Alt Text:** Always include alt text for the image to ensure accessibility and provide context if the image doesn\u2019t load.\n\u0915\u0940\u091f- **Responsive Design:** Use CSS styles to ensure the image is responsive and looks good on various screen sizes.\n\n### Why Not Embed Directly?\nMost email clients block iframes and JavaScript for security reasons, so embedding a Prezi directly into an email won\u2019t work. Using a linked thumbnail is a practical and reliable alternative.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
